The '''Star Temples''' were a series of ancient massive pyramid-shaped buildings constructed by the [[Kwa/Legends|Kwa]] around [[Infinity Gate]]s to protect them from intruders. If the Gate was ever activated, and thus subjecting Infinity to the [[Realspace/Legends|physical world]], the planet housing the equipment would collapse into the Infinity Gate, along with the surrounding planets, moons, and even suns. As the species fell from power throughout [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]], the Kwa sealed the Infinity Gate and the Star Temples and set [[whuffa worm]]s as guardians to protect the Temples.

In [[31 BBY/Legends|31 BBY]], the [[Nightsisters/Legends|Nightsisters]] succeeded in capturing the [[Prime Gate]] on [[Dathomir/Legends|Dathomir]] along with the Star Temple and slaughtered many [[Kwi]]. The Nightsisters had intended to access the secrets of the Infinity Gate and use its abilities to project a wave containing Infinity's power to destroy [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]], as well as surrounding planets and stars. However, their plot was [[Mission to Dathomir (Post–Naboo crisis)|thwarted]] by the [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]] [[Quinlan Vos/Legends|Quinlan Vos]], who, using his role as [[Temple Guardian]], redirected the deadly wave aimed at Coruscant back at the Infinity Gate, thus causing it to collapse on itself and destroy the Star Temple that housed it and the Realm of Infinity within. Only the scattered ruins of the Infinity Gate and the Star Temple were left.

